HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 864
By Lynn
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Roshanda Dana Heath
Walker.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the untimely passing of Roshanda Dana Heath Walker, formerly of Mt. Juliet; and
WHEREAS, Roshanda Walker was an accomplished attorney and a true intellectual
leader admired for her resilience, humor, and generosity; she approached life with intention and
heart, always striving to uplift others through her wisdom, compassion, and unwavering love;
and
WHEREAS, born in Miami, Florida, on July 27, 1979, Mrs. Walker was raised in Mt.
Juliet and educated in the Wilson County School System; she went on to earn her Bachelor of
Arts degree in Political Science, magna cum laude, from Howard University in 2001 and her
Juris Doctor degree from Thomas M. Cooley Law School in 2006; and
WHEREAS, early in her career, Roshanda Walker served as an attorney with the Dallas
County District Attorney's Office, gaining invaluable experience in public prosecution; her
professional journey combined strong academic credentials, public-sector prosecutorial work,
and private-sector litigation and defense, giving her a broad and balanced perspective on the
Texas legal system; and
WHEREAS, she practiced law with integrity, fairness, and empathy, earning the
admiration of colleagues and the trust of those she represented; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her service as a member of the bar, she dedicated herself to
community service through active membership in Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc., and Jack
and Jill of America, Inc.; her light and love transformed lives, inspiring joy and connection
wherever she went; and
HJR0864
012260
- 1 -

WHEREAS, introduced to Christ at an early age, Mrs. Walker was baptized as a child
and nurtured a lifelong journey of faith that she enjoyed with her family; and
WHEREAS, Roshanda Walker was deeply devoted to her family, and she always
endeavored to remain true to family values of the highest order; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Walker is lovingly remembered by her dear husband of twenty years,
Jason Walker; her children, Braylon Walker and Bailey Walker; her loving and very devoted
parents, Reverend James Tibbs and First Lady Doris Tibbs; her grandmother, Vera Heath; and
her sister, Michelle Malone; and
WHEREAS, she is further survived by her mother-in-law, Emma Walker; her father-in-
law, Gary (Brenda) Walker; her sisters-in-law, Robin and Asylin; her brothers-in-law, Garrick,
Pierce, and Elliott; her aunts, Effie Hayes, Georgia Cain, Minnie (Vester) McFarland, and
Barbara (Michael) Riley; her uncle, Bruce Tibbs; her father, Anthony Weatherford; and a host of
extended brothers, sisters, aunts, uncles, nieces, nephews, cousins, and devoted friends; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Walker was preceded in death by her mother, Theresa Heath; her
brother, Larry Overall; and her grandparents, Macie and Jimmie Tibbs, Charles Smith, and
Teresa Strowther; and
WHEREAS, Roshanda Walker leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity and probity
in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in all her
chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the bountiful life of this exceptional
public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Roshanda Dana Heath Walker, reflecting fondly
- 2 - 012260

upon her impeccable character and her stalwart commitment to living the examined life with
courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Mrs. Walker.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
